            <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.InstanceVariable_takesSentinelValuesFrom_SentinelValueDomain"
                              xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InstanceVariable_takesSentinelValuesFrom_SentinelValueDomain"
                              xmi:type="uml:Association">
               <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.InstanceVariable_takesSentinelValuesFrom_SentinelValueDomain-ownedComment"
                              xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InstanceVariable_takesSentinelValuesFrom_SentinelValueDomain-ownedComment"
                              xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                  <body>A represented variable may have more than one sets of sentinel value domains, one for each type of software platform on which related instance variables might be instantiated. All of the sentinel value domains must have sentinel conceptual domains that correspond exactly. This allows codes for missing values to be explicitly matched across platforms.</body>
                  <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.InstanceVariable_takesSentinelValuesFrom_SentinelValueDomain"/>
               </ownedComment>
               <name>InstanceVariable_takesSentinelValuesFrom_SentinelValueDomain</name>
