               </ownedAttribute>
               <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.RepresentedVariable-ownedAttribute-7"
                                xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#RepresentedVariable-ownedAttribute-7"
                                xmi:type="uml:Property">
                  <type xmi:idref="ddsc.SentinelValueDomain"/>
                  <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.RepresentedVariable-ownedAttribute-7-upperValue"
                               xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#RepresentedVariable-ownedAttribute-7-upperValue"
                               xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                     <value>*</value>
                  </upperValue>
                  <association xmi:idref="ddsc.RepresentedVariable_takesSentinelValuesFrom_SentinelValueDomain"/>
               </ownedAttribute>
            </packagedElement>
            <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.ReferenceVariable"
                              xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ReferenceVariable"
                              xmi:type="uml:Class">
               <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.ReferenceVariable-ownedComment"
                              xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ReferenceVariable-ownedComment"
                              xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                  <body>Definition
============
Variable that records values of multiple variables in the context of a data structure.
Variable playing the role of a variable value component.

Examples
==========
Consider two variables, i.e. income and age, with values appearing in the same column, e.g. 100000, 45, 85000, 34, etc. 
Values 100000, 45, 85000, 34 are reference values in the reference value domain corresponding to the reference variable.</body>
                  <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.ReferenceVariable"/>
               </ownedComment>
               <name>ReferenceVariable</name>
               <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ReferenceVariable-name"
