                     <body>Definition
============
Allows for unstructured content which may be an entry from an externally maintained controlled vocabulary.If the content is from a controlled vocabulary provide the code value of the entry, as well as a reference to the controlled vocabulary from which the value is taken. Provide as many of the identifying attributes as needed to adequately identify the controlled vocabulary. Note that DDI has published a number of controlled vocabularies applicable to several locations using the external controlled vocabulary entry structure. If the code portion of the controlled vocabulary entry is language specific (i.e. a list of keywords or subject headings) use language to specify that language. In most cases the code portion of an entry is not language specific although the description and usage may be managed in one or more languages. Use of shared controlled vocabularies helps support interoperability and machine actionability.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>ControlledVocabularyEntry</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryReference"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryReference"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>entryReference</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.Reference"/>
                     <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryReference-upperValue"
                                  xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryReference-upperValue"
                                  xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                        <value>*</value>
                     </upperValue>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryValue"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryValue"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>entryValue</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                     <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryValue-upperValue"
                                  xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ControlledVocabularyEntry-entryValue-upperValue"
                                  xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                        <value>*</value>
                     </upperValue>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry-name"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ControlledVocabularyEntry-name"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>name</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry-valueForOther"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ControlledVocabularyEntry-valueForOther"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>valueForOther</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry-vocabulary"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ControlledVocabularyEntry-vocabulary"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>vocabulary</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.Reference"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.Reference"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.Reference"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>Reference</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-ddiReference"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-ddiReference"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>ddiReference</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-deepLink"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-deepLink"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>deepLink</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.Selector"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-description"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-description"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>description</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-location"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-location"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>location</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.InternationalString"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-nonDdiReference"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-nonDdiReference"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>nonDdiReference</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier"/>
                     <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-nonDdiReference-upperValue"
                                  xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-nonDdiReference-upperValue"
                                  xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                        <value>*</value>
                     </upperValue>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-semantic"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-semantic"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>semantic</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-uri"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-uri"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>uri</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdAnyUri"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-validType"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-validType"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>validType</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                     <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.Reference-validType-upperValue"
                                  xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Reference-validType-upperValue"
                                  xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                        <value>*</value>
                     </upperValue>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
==========
Persistent, globally unique object identifier aligned with ISO/IEC 11179-6:2015, Information technology - Metadata registries (MDR) - Part 6: Registration, Annex A, Identifiers based on ISO/IEC 6523, http://standards.iso.org/ittf/PubliclyAvailableStandards/c060342_ISO_IEC_11179-6_2015.zip.
The uniqueness of an InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier (IRDI) is determined by the combination of the values of three identifying attributes.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-dataIdentifier"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-dataIdentifier"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>dataIdentifier</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-registrationAuthorityIdentifier"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-registrationAuthorityIdentifier"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>registrationAuthorityIdentifier</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-versionIdentifier"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalRegistrationDataIdentifier-versionIdentifier"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>versionIdentifier</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.Selector"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Selector"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.Selector-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Selector-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
==========
A resource which describes the segment of interest in a representation of a resource. This class is not used directly, only its subclasses. It is defined accordingly the related selector of the Web Annotation Vocabulary, see https://www.w3.org/TR/annotation-vocab/#selector.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.Selector"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>Selector</name>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.ObjectAttributeSelector"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ObjectAttributeSelector"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.ObjectAttributeSelector-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ObjectAttributeSelector-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
==========
A resource which describes a specific attribute of an object. It is defined in the style of selectors of the Web Annotation Vocabulary, see https://www.w3.org/TR/annotation-vocab/. The selector can be nested dependent on the structure of the referenced object.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.ObjectAttributeSelector"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>ObjectAttributeSelector</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ObjectAttributeSelector-refinedBy"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ObjectAttributeSelector-refinedBy"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>refinedBy</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ObjectAttributeSelector"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ObjectAttributeSelector-refinedByOrderNumber"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ObjectAttributeSelector-refinedByOrderNumber"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>refinedByOrderNumber</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#Integer"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.ObjectAttributeSelector-value"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#ObjectAttributeSelector-value"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>value</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.TextPositionSelector"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TextPositionSelector"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.TextPositionSelector-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TextPositionSelector-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
==========
Describes a range of text by recording the start and end positions of the selection in the object. Position 0 would be immediately before the first character, position 1 would be immediately before the second character, and so on. It is defined accordingly the related selector of the Web Annotation Vocabulary, see https://www.w3.org/TR/annotation-vocab/#textpositionselector.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.TextPositionSelector"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>TextPositionSelector</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.TextPositionSelector-end"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TextPositionSelector-end"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>end</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#Integer"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.TextPositionSelector-start"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TextPositionSelector-start"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>start</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#Integer"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalString"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalString"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalString-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalString-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Packaging structure for multilingual versions of the same string content, represented by a set of LanguageString. Only one LanguageString per language/scope type is allowed. Where an element of this type (InternationalString) is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains a different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.InternationalString"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>InternationalString</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalString-languageSpecificString"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalString-languageSpecificString"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>languageSpecificString</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.LanguageString"/>
                     <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.InternationalString-languageSpecificString-upperValue"
                                  xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#InternationalString-languageSpecificString-upperValue"
                                  xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                        <value>*</value>
                     </upperValue>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
A data type which describes a string specific to a language/scope combination. It contains the following attributes: language to designate the language, isTranslated with a default value of false to designate if an object is a translation of another language, isTranslatable with a default value of true to designate if the content can be translated, translationSourceLanguage to indicate the source languages used in creating this translation, translationDate, and scope which can be used to define intended audience or use such as internal, external, etc.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.LanguageString"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>LanguageString</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-content"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-content"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>content</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-isTranslatable"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-isTranslatable"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>isTranslatable</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#Boolean"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-isTranslated"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-isTranslated"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>isTranslated</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#Boolean"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-language"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-language"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>language</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdLanguage"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-scope"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-scope"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>scope</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-structureUsed"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-structureUsed"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>structureUsed</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-translationDate"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-translationDate"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>translationDate</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdDate"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-translationSourceLanguage"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-translationSourceLanguage"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>translationSourceLanguage</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdLanguage"/>
                     <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.LanguageString-translationSourceLanguage-upperValue"
                                  xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LanguageString-translationSourceLanguage-upperValue"
                                  xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                        <value>*</value>
                     </upperValue>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.BibliographicName"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#BibliographicName"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.BibliographicName-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#BibliographicName-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Personal names should be listed surname or family name first, followed by forename or given name. When in doubt, give the name as it appears, and do not invert. In the case of organizations where there is clearly a hierarchy present, list the parts of the hierarchy from largest to smallest, separated by full stops and a space. If it is not clear whether there is a hierarchy present, or unclear which is the larger or smaller portion of the body, give the name as it appears in the item. The name may be provided in one or more languages.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.BibliographicName"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>BibliographicName</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.BibliographicName-affiliation"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#BibliographicName-affiliation"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>affiliation</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.LabelForDisplay"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LabelForDisplay"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.LabelForDisplay-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LabelForDisplay-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
A structured display label. Label provides display content of a fully human readable display for the identification of the object.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.LabelForDisplay"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>LabelForDisplay</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LabelForDisplay-locationVariant"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LabelForDisplay-locationVariant"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>locationVariant</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LabelForDisplay-maxLength"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LabelForDisplay-maxLength"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>maxLength</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#Integer"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.LabelForDisplay-validDates"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#LabelForDisplay-validDates"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>validDates</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.DateRange"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.DateRange"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#DateRange"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.DateRange-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#DateRange-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Expresses a date/time range using a start date and end date (both with the structure of Date and supporting the use of ISO and non-ISO date structures). Use in all locations where a range of dates is required, i.e. validFor, embargoPeriod, collectionPeriod, etc.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.DateRange"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>DateRange</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.DateRange-endDate"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#DateRange-endDate"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>endDate</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.CombinedDate"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.DateRange-startDate"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#DateRange-startDate"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>startDate</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.CombinedDate"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.CombinedDate"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#CombinedDate"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.CombinedDate-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#CombinedDate-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Provides the structure of a single Date expressed in an ISO date structure along with equivalent expression in any number of non-ISO formats. While it supports the use of the ISO time interval structure this should only be used when the exact date is unclear (i.e. occurring at some point in time between the two specified dates) or in specified applications. Ranges with specified start and end dates should use the DateRange as a datatype. Commonly uses property names include: eventDate, issueDate, and releaseDate.

Explanatory notes
===================
Date allows one of a set of date-time (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss), date (YYYY-MM-DD), year-month (YYYY-MM), year (YYYY), time (hh:mm:ss) and duration (PnYnMnDnHnMnS), or time interval (YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss/YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss, YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss/PnYnMnDnHnMnS, PnYnMnDnHnMnS/ YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss) which is formatted according to ISO 8601 and backed supported by regular expressions in the BaseDateType. Time Zone designation and negative/positive prefixes are allowed as are dates before and after 0000 through 9999.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.CombinedDate"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>CombinedDate</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.CombinedDate-isoDate"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#CombinedDate-isoDate"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>isoDate</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdDate"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.CombinedDate-nonIsoDate"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#CombinedDate-nonIsoDate"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>nonIsoDate</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.NonIsoDate"/>
                     <upperValue xmi:id="ddsc.CombinedDate-nonIsoDate-upperValue"
                                  xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#CombinedDate-nonIsoDate-upperValue"
                                  xmi:type="uml:LiteralUnlimitedNatural">
                        <value>*</value>
                     </upperValue>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.CombinedDate-semantics"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#CombinedDate-semantics"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>semantics</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.NonIsoDate"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonIsoDate"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.NonIsoDate-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonIsoDate-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Used to preserve an historical date, formatted in a non-ISO fashion.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.NonIsoDate"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>NonIsoDate</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.NonIsoDate-calendar"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonIsoDate-calendar"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>calendar</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.NonIsoDate-dateContent"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonIsoDate-dateContent"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>dateContent</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.NonIsoDate-nonIsoDateFormat"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonIsoDate-nonIsoDateFormat"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>nonIsoDateFormat</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonDdiIdentifier"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonDdiIdentifier-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
A unique set of attributes, not conforming to the DDI identifier structure nor structured as a URI, used to identify some entity.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>NonDdiIdentifier</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier-managingAgency"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonDdiIdentifier-managingAgency"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>managingAgency</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier-type"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonDdiIdentifier-type"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier-value"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonDdiIdentifier-value"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>value</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.NonDdiIdentifier-version"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#NonDdiIdentifier-version"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>version</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.OrganizationName"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#OrganizationName"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.OrganizationName-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#OrganizationName-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
==========
Names by which the organization is known. Use the attribute isFormal with a value of True to designate the legal or formal name of the organization. Names may be typed with typeOfOrganizationName to indicate their appropriate usage.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.OrganizationName"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>OrganizationName</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.OrganizationName-abbreviation"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#OrganizationName-abbreviation"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>abbreviation</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.InternationalString"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.OrganizationName-effectiveDates"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#OrganizationName-effectiveDates"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>effectiveDates</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.DateRange"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.OrganizationName-isFormal"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#OrganizationName-isFormal"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>isFormal</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#Boolean"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.OrganizationName-typeOfOrganizationName"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#OrganizationName-typeOfOrganizationName"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>typeOfOrganizationName</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.TypedString"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TypedString"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.TypedString-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TypedString-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
TypedString combines a type with content defined as a simple string. May be used wherever a simple string needs to support a type definition to clarify its content.

Examples
==========
Content is a regular expression and the typeOfContent attribute is used to define the syntax of the regular expression content.

Explanatory notes
===================
This is a generic type + string where property name and documentation should be used to define any specification for the content. If international structured string content is required use TypedStructuredString.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.TypedString"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>TypedString</name>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.TypedString-content"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TypedString-content"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>content</name>
                     <type xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType"
                            href="http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/5.0.0/UML/PrimitiveTypes.xmi#String"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
                  <ownedAttribute xmi:id="ddsc.TypedString-typeOfContent"
                                   xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TypedString-typeOfContent"
                                   xmi:type="uml:Property">
                     <name>typeOfContent</name>
                     <type xmi:idref="ddsc.ControlledVocabularyEntry"/>
                  </ownedAttribute>
               </packagedElement>
            </packagedElement>
            <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.Enumerations"
                              xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#Enumerations"
                              xmi:type="uml:Package">
               <name>Enumerations</name>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.TrimValues"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TrimValues"
                                 xmi:type="uml:DataType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.TrimValues-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#TrimValues-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Specifies which spaces to remove from a data value (start, end, both, neither).</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.TrimValues"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>TrimValues</name>
               </packagedElement>
            </packagedElement>
            <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.XMLSchemaDataTypes"
                              xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#XMLSchemaDataTypes"
                              xmi:type="uml:Package">
               <name>XMLSchemaDataTypes</name>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.XsdAnyUri"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#XsdAnyUri"
                                 xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.XsdAnyUri-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#XsdAnyUri-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Primitive data type "anyURI" of the XML Schema data types.

Definition from XML Schema Part 2: Datatypes Second Edition:
"anyURI" represents a Uniform Resource Identifier Reference (URI). An "anyURI" value can be absolute or relative, and may have an optional fragment identifier (i.e., it may be a URI Reference). This type should be used to specify the intention that the value fulfills the role of a URI as defined by [RFC 2396], as amended by [RFC 2732]. For details see https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#anyURI.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdAnyUri"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>XsdAnyUri</name>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.XsdDate"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#XsdDate"
                                 xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.XsdDate-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#XsdDate-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Primitive data type "date" of the XML Schema data types.

Definition from XML Schema Part 2: Datatypes Second Edition:
"The value space of date consists of top-open intervals of exactly one day in length on the timelines of dateTime, beginning on the beginning moment of each day (in each timezone), i.e. '00:00:00', up to but not including '24:00:00' (which is identical with '00:00:00' of the next day). For nontimezoned values, the top-open intervals disjointly cover the nontimezoned timeline, one per day. For timezoned values, the intervals begin at every minute and therefore overlap." For details see https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#date.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdDate"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>XsdDate</name>
               </packagedElement>
               <packagedElement xmi:id="ddsc.XsdLanguage"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#XsdLanguage"
                                 xmi:type="uml:PrimitiveType">
                  <ownedComment xmi:id="ddsc.XsdLanguage-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:uuid="http://w3id.org/cdif/ddsc/1.0/ddsc/xmi/#XsdLanguage-ownedComment"
                                 xmi:type="uml:Comment">
                     <body>Definition
============
Derived data type "language" of the XML Schema data types.

Definition from XML Schema Part 2: Datatypes Second Edition:
"language" represents natural language identifiers as defined by by [RFC 3066]. The value space of "language" is the set of all strings that are valid language identifiers as defined [RFC 3066] . The lexical space of language is the set of all strings that conform to the pattern [a-zA-Z]{1,8}(-[a-zA-Z0-9]{1,8})*. The base type of "language" is token. https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#language.</body>
                     <annotatedElement xmi:idref="ddsc.XsdLanguage"/>
                  </ownedComment>
                  <name>XsdLanguage</name>
               </packagedElement>
            </packagedElement>
         </packagedElement>
      </packagedElement>
   </uml:Model>
</xmi:XMI>
